               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc>
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           <p>Twenty-two <material key="marmor">white marble</material> fragments, some joining, from the outer rim of a large <objectType key="circular crowning feature">circular feature</objectType> (outer diam. <dim type="diameter">3</dim> m, inner <dim type="diameter">2.55</dim>). The blocks were designed to be seen from below, and have elaborately ornamented trapezoidal panels on the underside (each <height>0.98</height> long); the panels each have a different pattern, which enables the grouping together of several fragments which do not join. The blocks are slightly convex, and the outer edge slopes outwards from bottom to top (H. <height unit="metre">0.16</height>); on it are a series of bosses with an ornamental cross (<height>0.40</height> apart).</p>
                        </support>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>The text runs in one line between the bosses, with a continuous line incised above and below it.</layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote>av. <height unit="metre">0.09</height>; deep triangular trenches; elongated and ornate. Colon for stop in a after <foreign xml:lang="grc">φύσιν</foreign>, and in b: semi-colon in a after <foreign xml:lang="grc">ΡΙΣ</foreign>; horizontal line over abbreviation in k.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
               </physDesc>
